places.name: Makka Masjid
places.address: HFXX+2V2 Makka Masjid, Eidgah Mohalla, Jharkhand 835223

featured_reviews.review_id:
So much attached with my childhood memories. I along with my friends used to visit there every year twice...
Oh I really miss the fun we had...
We used to went there on Eid-Ul-Fitr and Eid-Ul-Zuha. Both festivals brings happiness in our lives. Eidgah is decorated for offering Namaz and on those days(I mentioned above) people offer namaz together. Then they wish each other . And then Sewaiyan( special dish).
We really love going to friends home, eating Sewaiyan and having fun.
Eidgah is sorrounded with thelas of chaat , fuchka, ice cream , chawmin, Manchurian ,etc. And huge hustle is seen for buying these tasty fast foods.

featured_reviews.review_id: EID Al adha "Festival of Sacrifice"is the second of two Islamic holidays celebrated worldwide each year the other being Eid al-Fitr. In the Islamic lunar calendar, Eid al-Adha falls on the 10th day of Dhu al-Hijjah. In the international (Gregorian) calendar, the dates vary from year to year drifting approximately 11 days earlier each year.
